This paper deals with information delivery in a network of agents, which is a key issue in computer networks. The paper discusses routing protocols and examines different properties that define common routing algorithms. This topic falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Networked Systems (cs.NI), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
